  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "2001-04-04", 
    "text": "Social Security Benefits Fairness Act of 2001 - Amends title II (Old Age, Survivors and Disability Insurance) (OASDI) of the Social Security Act to provide that a monthly OASDI benefit shall be paid for the month in which the recipient dies, subject to a reduction of 50 percent if the recipient dies during the first 15 days of such month."
